<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Recovery Investigation Summary — {{ victim.name }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Confidential — Client Summary</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Recovery Investigation</div>
    <h1>Findings &amp;<br/>Next Steps</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Your stolen funds have been traced. Recoverable positions have
      been identified. This summary explains what we found, what
      it means for you, and the options you have from here.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared For</dt>
      <dd>{{ victim.name }}<span class="secondary">{% if victim.email %}{{ victim.email }}{% endif %}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared By</dt>
      <dd>{{ investigator.name }}<span class="secondary">{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>{{ investigator.email }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Case Reference</dt>
      <dd>{{ case_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Affected Wallet</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ victim.wallet_address }}</dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<div class="summary-box action">
  <p style="margin:0">
    <strong>Bottom line.</strong>
    Your wallet was traced across {{ summary.addresses_traced }} addresses on
    {{ chain_display }}. We identified recoverable stolen funds totaling
    <strong>{{ total_recoverable_freezable_usd }}</strong>
    currently held under {{ freezable_issuer_count }}
    {{ "issuer's" if freezable_issuer_count == 1 else "issuers'" }}
    authority, plus an additional
    <strong>{{ total_under_investigation_usd }}</strong>
    in positions pending issuer verification. Your options for
    pursuing recovery are explained in Section 3 below.
  </p>
</div>

<h2>1. What we did</h2>
<p>
  Following your engagement, we performed a forensic trace of the
  wallet at <span class="mono">{{ victim.wallet_address }}</span>
  on {{ chain_display }}. The trace followed every outbound
  transfer up to {{ max_depth }} {{ "hop" if max_depth == 1 else "hops" }}
  deep — meaning we tracked where your funds went, then where THOSE
  recipient wallets sent them, and so on. The trace identified
  {{ summary.transfers }} transactions involving
  {{ summary.addresses_traced }} unique addresses.
</p>
<p>
  The full forensic detail — every transaction hash, exact USD value,
  block timestamp, and chain-explorer link — is in the attached
  <span class="mono">trace_report.html</span>. The fund-flow diagram
  (<span class="mono">{{ flow_filename | default("flow.svg") }}</span>)
  visualizes where your money moved.
</p>

<h2>2. Where the money went</h2>
<p>
  The trace identified the following stablecoin holdings under
  authorities that have technical ability to freeze redemption.
  These are your most-likely recovery targets.
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Issuer</th>
      <th>Stablecoin</th>
      <th class="amount">Recoverable*</th>
      <th class="amount">Under Investigation</th>
      <th>Freeze Capability</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for entry in freezable_summary %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ entry.issuer }}</td>
      <td>{{ entry.token }}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ entry.total_usd_freezable }}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ entry.total_usd_suspected_only }}</td>
      <td>{{ entry.freeze_capability }}</td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
<p class="small">
  *<strong>Recoverable</strong>: positions confirmed in addresses with
  no matching customer-of-record at the issuer. These are the
  primary targets for an immediate freeze request.
  <strong>Under Investigation</strong>: positions in addresses where
  the issuer would need to verify customer records before status
  can be confirmed. Often promotes to Recoverable once the issuer
  responds.
</p>

<h2>3. Your options from here</h2>

<h3 style="margin-top:1.5em;">Option A: Engage Recupero for active recovery</h3>
<p>
  We coordinate the recovery process on your behalf — sending the
  prepared compliance letters to {{ freezable_issuer_count }}
  {{ "issuer" if freezable_issuer_count == 1 else "issuers" }},
  following up with their compliance teams, coordinating with the
  law-enforcement officer assigned to your case if you've filed,
  and reporting status back to you weekly for 30 days.
</p>
<div class="summary-box">
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.7em 0;">
    <strong>Engagement fee:</strong> {{ engagement_fee_text }}, plus
    {{ contingency_pct }}% of any funds actually recovered.
    The $499 you've already paid is credited toward the engagement fee.
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0;">
    <strong>What we promise:</strong> we will send each compliance
    letter, coordinate follow-up, and pursue every reasonable
    avenue. <strong>What we don't promise:</strong> a specific
    recovery amount or timeline. Issuer cooperation is voluntary
    until law-enforcement engagement compels it.
  </p>
</div>

<h3>Option B: Use the artifacts yourself</h3>
<p>
  All artifacts in this package are yours to use. You can take the
  law-enforcement handoff (the most detailed package) directly to
  the FBI, your local cyber-crime unit, or an attorney — they're
  professionally formatted for compliance and LE consumption. You
  can also forward the compliance freeze letters directly to each
  issuer's contact email (listed in the LE handoff). If you choose
  this path, you keep all artifacts and the case is closed on our
  side; we're available for clarification questions for 30 days at
  no additional charge.
</p>

<h2>4. Realistic timeline expectations</h2>
<p>
  Once a compliance freeze letter is sent to an issuer, typical
  response patterns we've observed:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Acknowledgement:</strong> within 24-72 hours for major
      issuers (Circle, Tether, Paxos). Smaller or less-experienced
      compliance desks can take 1-2 weeks.</li>
  <li><strong>Substantive response on freeze action:</strong> typically
      1-4 weeks. Major issuers prefer to wait for formal
      law-enforcement engagement before placing a hold. This is
      why filing with law enforcement (FBI / IC3 / state cyber
      unit) in parallel with the compliance request meaningfully
      improves outcomes.</li>
  <li><strong>Actual fund return:</strong> when it happens, typically
      weeks-to-months after the freeze is placed. Returns are
      processed by the issuer back to a verified victim wallet or
      to a court-appointed custodian, depending on the legal
      process used.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Important caveats</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Recovery is never guaranteed. Issuers have technical control
      but their cooperation is voluntary outside of formal legal
      process. Pursuing recovery without a law-enforcement
      complaint filed substantially reduces success rates.</li>
  <li>Funds marked <strong>Under Investigation</strong> may turn out
      to belong to the original KYC'd subscribers, not to the
      perpetrator. The issuer's KYC review determines that. We
      cannot predict the outcome of those reviews in advance.</li>
  <li>Partial recovery is the typical outcome. Even with a successful
      freeze, the amount returned is often less than the total
      identified — perpetrators often launder a portion through
      paths we cannot trace.</li>
  <li>If new fund movements occur after this report's date
      ({{ verified_at }}), the available recovery targets may
      change. We recommend acting within 30 days of this report.</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. How to proceed</h2>
<p>
  If you'd like to engage us for active recovery (Option A above),
  reply to this email or contact us at
  <a href="mailto:{{ investigator.email }}">{{ investigator.email }}</a>.
  We'll send you a one-page engagement letter that confirms the
  fee structure, the addresses we'll address, and the 30-day
  reporting cadence. The engagement begins when you sign and we've
  applied your $499 credit.
</p>
<p>
  If you'd like to use the artifacts yourself (Option B), no action
  is required from you — the package is yours. We recommend
  filing your complaint with law enforcement before forwarding
  the compliance letters to issuers; issuer freeze cooperation
  rates are several times higher with an active LE case number on
  file.
</p>

<div class="signature-block">
  <p style="margin:0 0 var(--space-md);">
    On behalf of {{ investigator.organization }},
  </p>
  <div class="signature-fields">
    <strong>{{ investigator.name }}</strong>
    Investigator of record · {{ investigator.email }}
  </div>
</div>


<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>Case {{ case_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Confidential.</span> Intended for {{ victim.name }}.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
